<title>UK: UK's Halifax makes debut at 774-1/2p.</title>
<headline>UK's Halifax makes debut at 774-1/2p.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Britain biggest mortgage lender, Halifax Building Society Plc started its first day's trade on the London Stock Exchange on Monday at 774-1/2p, valuing the group at around 19.4 billion stg.</p>
<p>At the current share price, the Halifax is ranked as the 16th largest listed UK company in terms of market capitalisation, according to data from Reuters Securities 3000.</p>
